  <span id="freeText16456646683952163114" style="display:none">I have mixed feelings for this one... <br /><b> <i> THINGS THAT REALLY PISSED ME OFF : </i></b> <br />1. If Nefer and Rameses (I'll never get the correct number of s) really had this 'beautiful understanding trusting' relationship, why does she hesitate to tell him the scandals going on in his own court ?? And why does she stop those who want to tell them to him instead, saying "He'll think I sent you out of jealousy." What ?<br />2. The protagonist somehow came across as PERFECT. No matter what happened, it was NEVER Nefer's fault. She is the beautiful/talented/misunderstood/used/intelligent soul everyone is against/using/hurting.Then there's Iset, who is just reduced to being a lesser Regina George, and Rameses... I'm not even going to say anything, I couldn't identify or relate with the characters AT ALL.<br />3. There was such a clear DISTINCTION between the BAD GUYS and the GOOD GUYS. The good guys were ALL GOOD and the bad ones ALL BAD. No one can be all bad or all good. When the good ones hurt the bad ones, its fine. When the bad ones hurt the good ones......Please stop.<br /><b> <i> THINGS I LIKED : </i></b> <br />1. Merit.<br />2. That this was a quick read.<br /> <br /><b> Keep Calm &amp; Read On </b></span>
