<div id="review_69112466" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/69112466" />
    <a title="Tara Chevrestt" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2544368-tara-chevrestt"><img alt="Tara Chevrestt" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1399003936p2/2544368.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/69112466?book_show_action=true">Aug 27, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tara Chevrestt" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tara Chevrestt" href="/user/show/2544368-tara-chevrestt">Tara Chevrestt</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2544368-tara-chevrestt?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2544368-tara-chevrestt?shelf=women-that-really-existed-fiction">women-that-really-existed-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2544368-tara-chevrestt?shelf=egypt">egypt</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer69112466" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15190053155024838204">90210 goes to Egypt!! That about sums it up. I found this novel to be juvenile. The entire novel is a cat fight between Nefertari (the daughter of Mutny, Nefertiti&apos;s sister) and a harem girl named Iset. Both Nefertari and Iset become wives of Ramses II and they are constantly fighting to be Chief Wife. While Ramses jumps bed to bed impregnating one or the other, the women resort to poision, lies, and use all their charms to lure the pharoah. There is some war thrown in here and there for good me</span>
  <span id="freeText15190053155024838204" style="display:none">90210 goes to Egypt!! That about sums it up. I found this novel to be juvenile. The entire novel is a cat fight between Nefertari (the daughter of Mutny, Nefertiti's sister) and a harem girl named Iset. Both Nefertari and Iset become wives of Ramses II and they are constantly fighting to be Chief Wife. While Ramses jumps bed to bed impregnating one or the other, the women resort to poision, lies, and use all their charms to lure the pharoah. There is some war thrown in here and there for good measure and even a chapter of pirates but the constant "love' drama had me picturing Tori and Tiffani with hennaed breasts fighting over Brian Austin Green wearing a golden pectorial. Michelle has a good writing style, but I enjoyed her "Nefertiti" more and the Mutny character from it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15190053155024838204" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


